
ifconfig [netwrkInterface] up/down  	-->set up or down
ifconfig -a		-->  to display network interfaces again

ifconfig [interface] [new ipaddress/mask] up		--> change ipaddress
	
route -n	--> show default gateway
route del default gw currentip	--> remove first current gw ipaddress
route add default gw newip	--> assign new ipaddress

to change netwrkIntface mac address:
ifconfig [interface] down	--> disable first
ifconfig [interface] hw ether newmacaddress example 08:00:27:51:05:09
ifconfig [interface] up	--> enable



---------------------------------
using ip command:
ip link set [interface] down/up		--> set
ip link show dev [interface]		--> show

ip address del 192.169.0.111/24 dev [interface] 	--> remove first ipaddress

ip address add 192.169.0.222/24 dev [interface] 	--> then add the new ip address 

ip route show	--> show default gateway
ip route del default	--> remove current gw ipaddress
ip route add default via newipaddress	--> assign new ipaddress


to change mac address:
ip link set dev [interface] address [newmacaddress]
ip link show dev [interface]
